/*
  ============================================================================
  WALT DISNEY WORLD DAILY TRIVIA - Questions Data File
  ============================================================================
  
  This file contains an array of trivia questions for the application.
  
  DATA STRUCTURE:
  Each question object must have the following properties:
  
  - id (string):
    Unique identifier for the question. Format suggestion: "{category}-{number}"
    Example: "mk-001" for first Magic Kingdom question
    
  - category (string):
    Must match one of these values (same as data-category in index.html):
    "magic-kingdom", "epcot", "hollywood-studios", "animal-kingdom", 
    "resorts", "dining", "transportation", "shows-entertainment", "history"
    
  - question (string):
    The trivia question text displayed to the user.
    
  - choices (array of strings):
    Four answer options. Order matters!
    These are displayed to the user in the order they appear here.
    
  - answerIndex (number):
    The index (0-3) of the correct answer within the choices array.
    Example: if choices[1] is correct, set answerIndex to 1
    
  - explanation (string, optional):
    Additional context or explanation. Currently unused but available
    for future features (e.g., showing explanation after answering).
  
  DAILY ROTATION:
  The application uses a deterministic hash function to select one question
  per category per day. The same question appears to all users on the same
  day, creating a shared daily challenge experience.
  
  FALLBACK:
  If this file fails to load (e.g., offline mode), the app falls back to
  a hardcoded questions array in js/app.js so the game continues to work.
  
  ============================================================================
*/

